## Formative Assessment: Check-In Levels

#### Check-in levels happen after students have had some initial practice with a skill, and allow for you, as the educator, to gauge how content is landing with your students. After releasing students to do independent work, sample their progress on check-in levels to understand how you might support your class.

## Summative Assessment: Assessment Levels

#### Assessment levels happen toward the end of a level progression, giving you data to review after a lesson has completed. Use these levels to gain a holistic view of student understanding and direction for how to adjust future instruction.

